OL,3,CParents who suffer death of a child
OL,4,Cgiven right to compassionate leave
OL,6,FThe changes, originally proposed by
OL,7,FDeputy Steve Ahier, mean parents can
OL,8,Ftake up to a fortnight away from work
OL,9,Fat any point during the first 56 weeks
OL,10,Fafter the child's death.
OL,12,FA government payment scheme will
OL,13,Fprovide financial support for any
OL,14,Fpotential lost wages, including those
OL,15,Fwho are self-employed.
OL,17,FDeputy Feltham said: "For any parent,
OL,18,Fthe death of a child is a tragedy and
OL,19,Fno amount of time off work or
OL,20,Ffinancial assistance will make up for
OL,21,Fit.
